#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Cīvaravagga → kathinavagga (^pi-tv-pvr1.1#82 [Kattha­paññat­ti­vāra/4. Kathinavagga] ^pi-tv-pvr1.2#20 [Katāpattivāra/4. Kathinavagga])
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

# NOTE: Here, and in the heading to _nissaggiya pācittiya 3_ (and also at the end of each of these rules), I translate _kathina_ as “robe-making season” rather than “robe-making ceremony,” since this is the contextual meaning in these rules.
#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:0.5"
msgid "1. Kathinasikkhāpada"
msgstr "1. The training rule on the robe-making season"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.195, pts-vp-en2.1, ms1V_1861
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:0.6"
msgid "Ime kho panāyasmanto tiṃsa nissaggiyā pācittiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti."
msgstr "Venerables, these thirty rules entailing relinquishment and confession come up for recitation."

#. HTML: </p><hr><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-cs-bu-np1.1, ms1V_1862
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati gotamake cetiye."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī at the Gotamaka Shrine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ ticīvaraṃ anuññātaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time the Master had allowed the three robes for the monks."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.3"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā ticīvaraṃ anuññātan”ti aññeneva ticīvarena gāmaṃ pavisanti, aññena ticīvarena ārāme acchanti, aññena ticīvarena nahānaṃ otaranti."
msgstr "Knowing that this was the case, the monks from the group of six entered the village in one set of three robes, stayed in the monastery in another set, and went to bathe in yet another set."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.6"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekacīvaraṃ dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six have extra robes?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1863
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.8"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, atirekacīvaraṃ dhārethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you have extra robes?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.9"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.10"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.3
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.11"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, atirekacīvaraṃ dhāressatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you have extra robes?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.12"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.13"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.13a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.14"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu atirekacīvaraṃ dhāreyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk has extra robe-cloth, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-en2.4, ms1V_1865
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.15"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli3.196
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.16"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato ānandassa atirekacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards robe-cloth was given to Venerable Ānanda."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.17"
msgid "Āyasmā ca ānando taṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa dātukāmo hoti."
msgstr "He wanted to give it to Venerable Sāriputta"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.18"
msgid "Āyasmā ca sāriputto sākete viharati."
msgstr "who was staying at Sāketa."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.19"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "Knowing that the Buddha had laid down a rule against having extra robe-cloth, Ānanda thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.20"
msgid "“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.21"
msgid "‘na atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretabban’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.22"
msgid "Idañca me atirekacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.23"
msgid "Ahañcimaṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato sāriputtassa dātukāmo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.24"
msgid "Āyasmā ca sāriputto sākete viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.25"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "“What should I do in this situation?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.26"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He told the Master, and the Master said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.27"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ panānanda, sāriputto āgacchissatī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long is it, Ānanda, before Sāriputta returns?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.28"
msgid "“Navamaṃ vā, bhagavā, divasaṃ dasamaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "“Nine or ten days, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.29"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.30"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dasāhaparamaṃ atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, you should keep extra robe-cloth for ten days at the most."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.31"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.31a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: In addition to meaning a finished robe, according to the definition of _cīvara_ below it also refers to pieces of robe-cloth. This means that I have to vary my translation depending on the context.
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: kathine → kaṭhine (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1867, pts-vp-en2.5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.32"
msgid "“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine dasāhaparamaṃ atirekacīvaraṃ dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, a monk should keep extra robe-cloth for ten days at the most."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:1.33"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-np1.3.1, pts-vp-en2.6, ms1V_1868
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.1"
msgid "Niṭṭhitacīvarasminti"
msgstr "When his robe is finished:"

# NOTE: This refers to the robe-cloth received during the robe-making season. For details see [](Mv.7.2-7.12).
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.2"
msgid "bhikkhuno cīvaraṃ kataṃ vā hoti naṭṭhaṃ vā vinaṭṭhaṃ vā daḍḍhaṃ vā cīvarāsā vā upacchinnā."
msgstr "the monk has made a robe, or the robe-cloth has been lost, destroyed, or burnt, or he has abandoned his expectation of receiving further robe-cloth."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_1869
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.3"
msgid "Ubbhatasmiṃ kathineti"
msgstr "The robe-making season has ended:"

# NOTE: For an explanation of this see [](Mv.7.1.7) and [](Mv.7.2-7.12).
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.4"
msgid "aṭṭhannaṃ mātikānaṃ aññatarāya mātikāya ubbhataṃ hoti, saṃghena vā antarā ubbhataṃ hoti."
msgstr "it has ended according to one of the eight headings or the Order has ended it, whichever comes first."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1870
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.5"
msgid "Dasāhaparamanti"
msgstr "For ten days at the most:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: dasāhaparamatā → dasāha­parama­tāya (si)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.6"
msgid "dasāhaparamatā dhāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "it should be kept for ten days at a maximum."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-en2.7, ms1V_1871
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.7"
msgid "Atirekacīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Extra robe-cloth:"

# NOTE: “Transferred” is a rendering of _vikappita_. The explanation given at _pācittiya_ 59 seems to make it clear that _vikappanā_ refers to a change in ownership. The word commentary specifically says that the item is given to someone else and that the monk giving it up may use it only if he takes their belonging on trust.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.8"
msgid "anadhiṭṭhitaṃ avikappitaṃ."
msgstr "robe-cloth that is not determined, nor transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_1872
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.9"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

# NOTE: The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp, see [](Mv.8.3.1).
# NOTE: This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (_sugata_) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see [](Kkh.94.4) and BMC I, pp.565-566.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.1.10"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ, vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-np1.3.2, ms1V_1873
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.1"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ hotīti"
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that […] entailing relinquishment:"

# NOTE: According to the commentary this means the tenth dawn after one received the robe(cloth, see [](Sp.3.639.27)
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.2"
msgid "ekādase aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "it becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the eleventh day."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.5"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching the Order, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.6"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ dasāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe-cloth that I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.7"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.8"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.9"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

#. VAR: dātabbaṃ → hotīti idaṃ padaṃ sabba­pottha­kesu atthi, sikkhāpade pana natthi,
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.10"
msgid "Nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "The relinquished robe-cloth is then to be given back:"

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1874
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.11"
msgid "“Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.12"
msgid "Idaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno nissaggiyaṃ saṃghassa nissaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "This robe-cloth that was to be relinquished by monk so-and-so has been relinquished to the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.13"
msgid "Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho imaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dadeyyā”ti."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should give this robe-cloth back to monk so-and-so.’"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc15, pts-vp-pli3.197, ms1V_1875
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.14"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā sambahule bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassu vacanīyā—"
msgstr "After approaching several monks, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.15"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ dasāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe-cloth that I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.16"
msgid "Imāhaṃ āyasmantānaṃ nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the venerables.’"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.17"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.18"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.19"
msgid "Nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "The relinquished robe-cloth is then to be given back:"

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_1876
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.20"
msgid "“Suṇantu me āyasmantā."
msgstr "‘Let the venerables listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.21"
msgid "Idaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno nissaggiyaṃ āyasmantānaṃ nissaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "This robe-cloth that was to be relinquished by monk so-and-so has been relinquished to you."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.22"
msgid "Yadāyasmantānaṃ pattakallaṃ, āyasmantā imaṃ cīvaraṃ itthannāmassa bhikkhuno dadeyyun”ti."
msgstr "If it seems appropriate to you, you should give this robe-cloth back to monk so-and-so.’"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="kamma">
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_1877
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.23"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "After approaching a single monk, that monk should put his upper robe over one shoulder, squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.24"
msgid "“idaṃ me, āvuso, cīvaraṃ dasāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘This robe-cloth that I have kept over ten days is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.25"
msgid "Imāhaṃ āyasmato nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to you.’"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.26"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.27"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The confession should be received by that monk."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.28"
msgid "Nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ dātabbaṃ—"
msgstr "The relinquished robe-cloth is then to be given back:"

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:3.2.29"
msgid "“imaṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato dammī”ti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc18, pts-cs-bu-np1.4, ms1V_1878
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.1"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante atikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days and he perceives it as more than ten days, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.2"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante vematiko, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.3"
msgid "Dasāhātikkante anatikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than ten days, but he perceives it as less than ten days, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.4"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been determined, but he perceives it as determined, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.5"
msgid "Avikappite vikappitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been transferred, but he perceives it as transferred, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.6"
msgid "Avissajjite vissajjitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been given away, but he perceives it as given away, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.7"
msgid "Anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been lost, but he perceives it as lost, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.8"
msgid "Avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.9"
msgid "Adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been burnt, but he perceives it as burnt, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.10"
msgid "Avilutte viluttasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_1879
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.11"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses a robe-cloth that should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.12"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante atikkantasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days, but he perceives it as more than ten days, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.13"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.14"
msgid "Dasāhānatikkante anatikkantasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than ten days and he perceives it as less than ten days, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_1880
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.15"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.16"
msgid "antodasāhaṃ adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within ten days it has been determined, transferred, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.17"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:4.18"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc21, pts-cs-bu-np1.5, ms1V_1881
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ na denti."
msgstr "At that time monks from the group six did not give back relinquished robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:5.2"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master."

#. HTML: <span class="rule">
#. VAR: () → () s1-3 potthakesu
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.11,
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:5.3"
msgid "() “Na, bhikkhave, nissaṭṭhacīvaraṃ na dātabbaṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, relinquished robe-cloth should be given back."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:5.4"
msgid "Yo na dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If a monk does not give it back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc22, ms1V_1882
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np1:5.5"
msgid "Kathinasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on the robe-making season, is finished."
